o pull this off, as I am faced with a fully poped zone and my entire raid in the ferrot because of this little problem with the zerver crash.  Please dont monk me too much<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Eoral Solis<br>
Servant of Evoluxa <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukrilandawnfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krilan Dawnfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/18/01 12:31:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fear Portal Breaks</span><hr size=1> You dont have to do a Portal Break it's possible to run people 2-3 at a time to the Safe spot and have them camp out and send the next 2-3. Just buff them cast invis/sow make sure you get a cleric there. Most of the raid should make it. you do CR while you pull as the raid starts with people who died closer to the portal waiting in Chat because thats a hard spot to CR from at the start of a raid untill you've pulled some mobs. If you have a Druid/Ranger who if very familiar with training mobs in Fear so you can pick them off you coul send one or two in to grab the mobs from the path to the SS to make it easier for everyone else to make the SS alive.<br>
<br>
This is how most raids had to do it before Fear became perma camped. Most of the time you should end up with a majority of the raid reaching the SS alive and it's not unlike running to the Hate Safespot if any raids still do that.<br>
<br>
For a portal break I wouldnt attempt it without atleast 2 55+ Enchancters, the higher the better. It just involves buffing everyone casting invis  and zoning 2 groups at a time (To prevent LD upon zoning) and running to the wall to the left of the portal and then kill what ever comes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubarrinsoulburner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Barrin Soulburner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>some newbie</span><br>  Posts: 556<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/18/01 12:32:56 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://eq.geauxonline.com/watchers/barrin.jpg h=496 w=293></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fear Portal Breaks</span><hr size=1> Not super tough.  Biggest thing is staggering groups so you don't crash the zone / everyone that zones in goes LD.<br>
<br>
Buff everyone up (assuming you are taking 30-36 people here).  Invis / See invis on everyone.  Zone groups in 2 groups at a time in 30 second intervals.<br>
<br>
Make sure to tell everyone:  When you zone in, turn left 90%, run to the wall.  Meet up at the wall, fight stuff that comes to camp until it nothing is in camp.  Requires decent enchanters and people that know how to use assist.  Once you have broken camp, pull as you normally would.<br>
<br>
Its really not that hard...something I don't think Evoluxa will have much of a problem with.<br>
<br>
Main problems you may have:<br>
<br>
1. People don't get the &quot;Zone in, turn left 90%, run to wall.&quot; part and train the FF house on the group.<br>
2. You don't have enough enchanters. (try to get 3 or 4 if you haven't done this before)<br>
3. Everyone zones in at the same time and the zone crashes/everyone goes LD.<br>
<br>
Its really not that hard, and it speeds up the raid a lot.<br>
<br>
Barrin<br>
-Watchers <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubarrinsoulburner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Barrin Soulburner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>some newbie</span><br>  Posts: 557<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/18/01 12:34:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fear Portal Breaks</span><hr size=1> You could also do North wall break like Krilan said, that works.  Theres a really good map around somewhere?  Someone might be able to post a link. (little help!) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueoralsolis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EoralSolis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 152<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/18/01 1:17:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fear Portal Breaks</span><hr size=1> THanks guys, I appreciate the info.  We actually managed to sneak a team of 10 to the SS just as the GM repoped the zone (WTB Clean Shorts) and we have a cleric parked there for rezzes.  I appreciate the info, for though we have 3 chanters, we dont have 2 over 55 and though my crew is great, I am very lerry of Portal breaks as I know how badly folks have f***ed them up in the past.  Thank you again for your information.<br>
